----field----
field: {446A339B-E1D9-4DE1-8B5E-DB7942EF1723}
name: Body
key: body
content-length: 1410

<p>Sanofi has revealed that Olivier Brandicourt, confirmed as Sanofi's new CEO, will be paid a salary of &euro;1.2m a year when he joins the French firm at the start of April, plus a performance-related bonus of 150% of his salary, subject to meeting certain objectives. He is also eligible for stock options and performance shares. </p><p>Dr Brandicourt will also receive a &euro;4m 'golden handshake': &euro;2m when he joins the company, and &euro;2m in January 2016, if he's still with Sanofi at that time. This is compensation for loss of benefits at Bayer, said Sanofi. Dr Brandicourt is currently CEO and chairman of Bayer Healthcare, having joined the company from Pfizer in 2013.</p><p>French politicians find Dr Brandicourt's remuneration package excessive, with government spokesperson Stephane Le Foll branding it "incomprehensible."</p><p><p><b><i>Related stories:</i></b></p><p><a href="http://www.scripintelligence.com/home/Its-official-Bayers-Brandicourt-is-Sanofis-new-CEO-356855" target="_new">It's official: Bayer's Brandicourt is Sanofi's new CEO</a></p><p><a href="http://www.scripintelligence.com/business/Brandicourt-to-abandon-Bayer-for-Sanofi-356797" target="_new">Brandicourt to abandon Bayer for Sanofi?</a></p><p><a href="http://www.scripintelligence.com/business/Viehbacher-received-3m-payoff-from-Sanofi-356344" target="_new">Viehbacher received &euro;3m payoff from Sanofi</a></p>
